<doc>
  <member name="D3D10_BUFFER_RTV">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies the elements from a <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-programming-guide-resources-types">buffer</a> resource to use in a render-target view.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>A render-target view is a member of a render-target-view description (see <see cref="D3D10_RENDER_TARGET_VIEW_DESC" />). Create a render-target view by calling <see cref="ID3D10Device.CreateRenderTargetView" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-reference-resource-structures">Resource Structures</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D10_BUFFER_RTV.FirstElement">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/WinProg/windows-data-types">UINT</a></b></para>
      <para>Number of bytes between the beginning of the buffer and the first element to access.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D10_BUFFER_RTV.ElementOffset">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/WinProg/windows-data-types">UINT</a></b></para>
      <para>The offset of the first element in the view to access, relative to element 0.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D10_BUFFER_RTV.NumElements">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/WinProg/windows-data-types">UINT</a></b></para>
      <para>The total number of elements in the view.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D10_BUFFER_RTV.ElementWidth">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/WinProg/windows-data-types">UINT</a></b></para>
      <para>The width of each element (in bytes). This can be determined from the format stored in the render-target-view description.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>